                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/22178</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tampico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-21T18:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Banditti last night attacked terminals of Eureka Coast Oil Co., American, and
                    Corona Co., Dutch Shell, three miles from Tampico. Attacked wife of British
                    employee of Dutch company, and were finally beaten off by armed employees of
                    Eureka Coast Co. Several Mexicans killed or wounded. Embassy advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
